title: 'Why were monks with valid docus stopped from international travel?'
Cops probe how 'missing son' had info on 2 families
Air quality in Delhi improves to best since October 29
Bangladesh HC acquits Zia’s son in 2004 grenade attack cases
Arrested AAP MLA Balyan, gangster Sangwan had 40 calls last year, claim cops
GST mop-up in November up 8.5% to ₹1.8 lakh crore

description: US President-elect Donald Trump threatened 100% tariffs on BRICS countries if they pursue new currency alternatives to the US Dollar, citing its dominant role in foreign exchange reserves and trade. However, experts argue that such tariffs could harm US consumers and global trade, with many nations driven to 'de-dollarise' due to geopolitical and economic incentives.
title: What’s behind Trump’s threat of 100% tariff on Brics?

description: Scheduled surgeries and appointments of Bangladeshi patients in Kolkata's private hospitals are being canceled or deferred due to ongoing turmoil. Hospitals like Peerless, Desun, BP Poddar, and Manipal have reported significant declines in Bangladeshi patients, leading to an increased use of online consultations. Hospitals are ensuring continuity of care through telemedicine services.
title: Bangladeshi patients cancel surgeries at Kolkata hospistals amid turmoil
Day 1 of IIT-B placements: 2.2cr offer from Dutch co

description: Vivek Ramaswamy criticizes the US immigration system for rewarding dishonesty over genuine asylum claims. He stresses the need for reform, echoing Trump’s policies on securing borders and enforcing the rule of law. Ramaswamy emphasizes lawful entry and opposes benefits for undocumented immigrants.
title: 'Willingness to lie to govt': Vivek Ramaswamy criticises US immigration system

description: A 'mahapanchayat' organized by Devbhoomi Vichar Manch in Uttarkashi demanded stringent action against unlawful religious structures. BJP MLA T Raja Singh urged CM Dhami to adopt strict measures against illegal mosques, similar to UP CM Yogi Adityanath. The event, attended by over 350 people, concluded peacefully with no reports of violence or hate speech.
title: Emulate Yogi, bring in bulldozers: Uttarkashi mahapanchayat's message to CM Dhami
Adopt 'SMART' policing: PM Modi to cops amid rising digital frauds

description: Hundreds of Bangladeshi nationals, including Sudharani Mondal, are rushing back to Bangladesh through the Petrapole border, fearing political turmoil may lead to the closure of the border. Although BSF officials deny any border closure, they remain vigilant against illegal infiltration. The situation remains tense, with families seeking to reunite amid the unrest.
title: Long queue at border checkpost as Bangladeshi nationals rush to go back home
Supreme Court stalls razing of illegal structure in Mumbai
Indians stranded at Kuwait airport after snag leads to flight diversion
Prayagraj set to welcome 40 crore for Maha Kumbh '25

description: Cyclone Fengal caused record-breaking rainfall in Puducherry, leading to significant flooding and power outages. The Indian Army and Coast Guard rescued over 100 people. Schools and colleges are serving as relief centers. Villupuram district also experienced severe flooding, with the highest rainfall recorded at 50 cm. Relief efforts are ongoing in affected areas.
title: Cyclone Fengal triggers record rain in Puducherry in 30 years

description: Canada has ended the SDS visa scheme, which provided a fast-track for Indian students. Now, students applying for regular study permits will only need to pay six months' tuition upfront and show sufficient funds for living expenses. This change aims to ensure equal access and make studying in Canada more affordable.
title: Canada's scrapping of SDS visa to help Indian students: Govt in LS

description: BJP state president K Annamalai asserts that actor Vijay's political entry won't harm BJP's prospects in Tamil Nadu, suggesting Vijay's appeal aligns more with Dravidian parties. Meanwhile, Annamalai welcomes Vijay's entry, indicating increased political options for the populace. Annamalai criticizes DMK's dynastic politics, proclaiming that 2026 will end such politics and expressing confidence in BJP's strength in TN.
title: BJP not scared of Vijay's political entry: Tamil Nadu state chief Annamalai

description: External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar is set to update Lok Sabha on India's developments with China, following a disengagement agreement reached on Oct 21 that restores pre-friction patrolling and grazing in Depsang and Demchok. This accord led to a landmark meeting between PM Modi and President Xi Jinping. Eastern Ladakh disengagement developments continue as per the agreement.
title: EAM Jaishankar to brief LS on recent developments in ties with China

description: President-elect Donald Trump appoints Kash Patel as FBI Director, prompting social media calls for the declassification of contentious documents such as the 'Epstein list' and 'Diddy list.' Elon Musk supports the push for transparency, aligning with Patel's advocacy for revealing sensitive information for public accountability.
title: Musk backs call for transparency after Kash Patel's appointment

description: J&K BJP leaders demand action against PDP president Mehbooba Mufti for her controversial remarks comparing the treatment of minorities in India to Bangladesh. They describe her statements as anti-national and divisive. BJP's Tarun Chugh accuses Mehbooba of ideological bankruptcy, asserting her claims of India's secular foundation shaking are baseless and reflect frustration over electoral failures.
title: BJP flays Mehbooba for equating Bangla minorities with India

description: RSS chief Mohan Bhagwat warned that social groups with birth rates below 2.1 could face extinction, stressing the importance of maintaining population levels for survival. He highlighted India's inclusive cultural ethos and the need for unity despite differences. Bhagwat also emphasized that discrimination based on caste has no place in Indian religious scriptures.
title: To survive, a community needs at least 3 kids per couple: RSS chief

description: Jaydeep Mukherjee, director of Nasa Florida Space Grant Consortium, warned that a Chinese lunar landing before the US would be embarrassing for America. He highlighted ongoing technical issues and cost overruns with Nasa's Artemis missions. Mukherjee stated that solving these problems is critical to achieving the 2026 target for a manned US lunar landing.
title: ‘Shameful if Chinese astronauts on moon before US’
Will back any decision taken by Modi, Shah on CM: Eknath Shinde

description: Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge criticizes BJP's top leaders for using divisive tactics, including mosque surveys to find temples. He references Mohan Bhagwat's 2022 remark against widespread searches and the Places of Worship Act 1991. Kharge queries BJP's stance on structures built by Muslims. This comes amid violence in Uttar Pradesh's Sambhal related to a mosque survey.
title: Pay heed to Bhagwat words on masjid surveys: Kharge to BJP

description: Assam CM Himanta Biswa Sarma stated he would ban beef if Congress provides a written request. His comments came amid allegations that BJP distributed beef to win the Muslim-dominated Samaguri constituency bypoll. Sarma questioned Congress' long-term success in the region and challenged them to support a beef ban in writing if they were sincere.
title: Will ban beef in Assam if Cong files written request: Himanta

description: US President-elect Donald Trump demanded a commitment from BRICS nations, including China, India, and Russia, to not create or support a new currency to replace the US dollar, threatening 100% tariffs and restricted access to the US economy if ignored. Trump's warning follows BRICS' discussions on 'de-dollarisation'.
title: 'Find another sucker': Trump warns Brics it will lose access to US if it dumps 'mighty' dollar

description: Ten Kuki-Zo youths, nine adults and one minor, were killed in an alleged gunfight with CRPF on November 11 in Manipur. Post-mortem exams indicated multiple bullet wounds, mostly from behind, without signs of torture. The victims were believed to be militants by police, while the ITLF claims they were village volunteers amid ongoing ethnic violence.
title: Kuki-Zo youths shot multiple times, mostly on back in Manipur: Autopsy

description: Government forces lost control of Aleppo to the Islamist-dominated rebel alliance for the first time since the conflict began in 2011. The lightning assault was led by Hayat Tahrir al-Sham and coincided with a ceasefire in Lebanon. Kurdish forces expanded their control, exacerbating tensions with the rebels.
title: Syrian govt loses control of second-largest city Aleppo for first time since 2011

description: Shoaib Akhtar addressed the ongoing situation regarding the ICC Champions Trophy 2025 in Pakistan. He emphasized Pakistan's reasonable stance on hosting rights and revenue. He also highlighted the importance of fostering friendly relations by participating in future tournaments in India. Pakistan agreed to a hybrid model for the Champions Trophy, with India's matches to be played in Dubai.
title: 'Hybrid model pehele hi sign ho gaya tha': Shoaib Akhtar

description: Devendra Fadnavis has reportedly been finalised as Maharashtra's next chief minister, with the BJP legislature party set to meet on December 2 or 3. The new Mahayuti government's swearing-in ceremony is scheduled for December 5, with Prime Minister Narendra Modi expected to attend.
title: 'Devendra Fadnavis finalised as Maharashtra CM,' says BJP leader

description: Kash Patel, a staunch supporter of the Ram Mandir and fierce critic of the "deep state," has been nominated by Donald Trump as FBI Director, symbolising a unique convergence of Indic and American populist narratives. Known for co-authoring the "Nunes Memo," Patel has challenged institutional biases and accused the US justice system of favouring elites while targeting conservatives. A loyal advocate of Trump’s America First agenda, Patel’s rise disrupts perceptions of Trump’s cabinet as homogeneously Christian. His vocal support for US-India ties and cultural identity, combined with his anti-establishment stance, underscores his role as a disruptive force in modern politics.
title: Meet Kash Patel, Trump's pro-Ram Mandir FBI chief pick

description: Several Indian passengers are stranded at Kuwait Airport after their Gulf Air Bahrain-Manchester flight was diverted due to a technical issue. Indians, not eligible for visa on arrival in Kuwait, are stuck at the airport while other nationals have left. The Indian embassy is assisting but hotels are almost full due to the GCC Summit.
title: Many Indians stranded after Gulf Air flight’s emergency landing in Kuwait

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi emphasized the importance of addressing digital frauds, cyber-crimes, and AI technology threats, urging police to leverage Artificial Intelligence and 'Aspirational India.' During the 59th All India Police Chiefs' Conference, he advocated for SMART policing and technology use to ease constabulary workloads, focusing on urban initiatives and border security with Bangladesh and Myanmar.
title: 'Harness double AI power', PM tells police on threats from digital fraud

description: Ishan Kishan, a key player for Mumbai Indians since 2018, was not retained by the team ahead of the 2025 IPL auction. Hardik Pandya shared a heartfelt message appreciating Kishan's contributions. Ishan was bought by Sunrisers Hyderabad for Rs 11.25 crore. Kishan expressed gratitude to MI and its fans in an emotional Instagram post.
title: 'You always be MI's pocket-dynamo': Pandya's message for Kishan

description: Shiv Sena MLA Gulabrao Patil suggested that the party could have gained more seats without Ajit Pawar's NCP in the Mahayuti alliance. Patil praised Eknath Shinde's leadership, showing no dissatisfaction despite Pawar’s inclusion. As Mahayuti prepares to announce the next Maharashtra CM, Shinde has pledged support for the BJP's decision.
title: 'Party could have won 90-100 seats if not for Ajit Pawar's NCP': Shinde Sena MLA

description: Indian pacer Mohammed Shami shared a video on Instagram, showcasing his dedication to cricket. After an injury layoff, Shami returned, playing a crucial role in Bengal's victories in the Ranji Trophy and Syed Mushtaq Ali T20 Trophy. His disciplined bowling helped Bengal secure wins, while his passion for cricket remains unwavering.
title: 'Life just doesn’t make sense without ... ': Shami sweats it out in nets

description: Bangladesh's immigration authorities at the Benapole border denied entry to 54 Iskcon members despite valid documents, citing the absence of specific government approval. This follows heightened scrutiny of Iskcon amidst the arrest of Hindu leader Chinmoy Krishna Das and subsequent tension and protests among Hindu minorities in Bangladesh.
title: B'desh stops dozens of Iskcon members from crossing into India

description: Kannada actress Shobhitha Shivanna, aged 30, allegedly committed suicide in her Hyderabad home. The actress, known for her prominence in television and film, had moved to Hyderabad post-marriage. She left behind a successful career and shocked her fans and the industry with her unexpected death.
title: Kannada actress Shobitha Shivanna dies by suicide at 30

description: Jamia Millia Islamia issued a notice banning protests or slogan-raising on campus without prior approval. Students defying this rule may face disciplinary action. The notice, similar to one issued in August 2022, aims to maintain an academic environment. All India Students' Association has criticised the directive as an attack on the university's autonomy.
title: Jamia cracks down on protests by students, issues warning

description: In a thrilling Game 6 of the World Chess Championship, 18-year-old Indian challenger D Gukesh drew with the defending champion Ding Liren of China after 46 moves. Both are level at 3 points each, needing 4.5 points to win. The match continues with eight games remaining, and Ding Liren appears to be gaining confidence.
title: D Gukesh forces draw against Ding Liren in Game 6

description: Priyanka Gandhi Vadra pledged to pressure both the Indian central government and Kerala's Chief Minister for rehabilitation of Wayanad landslide victims. She emphasized prioritizing aid over politics and encouraged tourism to show the region's safety and beauty. During her visit, she recounted meeting a resilient local survivor, highlighting her commitment to the community's future.
title: 'Putting pressure on centre': MP Priyanka on aid for Wayanad landslide

description: Rahul Gandhi criticised the central government over the seven-quarter low GDP growth rate of 5.4%. He highlighted economic distress among farmers, laborers, and the middle class, citing stagnating incomes, rising inflation, and unemployment. Gandhi emphasized that measures like demonetization and GST have harmed demand and manufacturing. He called for new economic thinking to ensure equal opportunities for all.
title: 'New thinking needed': Rahul Gandhi slams Centre over low GDP growth rate

description: Bollywood's 2024 box office has seen highs with hits like Stree 2, Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3, and Singham Again, but faced noteworthy flops including Indian 2 and Bade Miyan Chote Miyan. The year’s revenue shows a decline compared to 2023. Anticipation remains high for upcoming releases in December, expected to boost the industry's overall performance.
title: Stree 2, Pushpa 2, Kalki 2898 AD: Bollywood's 2024 box office journey

description: Dua Lipa electrified fans at the Zomato Feeding India Concert in Mumbai by performing a mashup of her hit 'Levitating' with Shah Rukh Khan's 'Woh Ladki Jo' from 'Baadshah.'
title: Dua Lipa's Levitating X Woh Ladki Jo meme mashup goes viral

description: A groom’s light-hearted approach at his wedding, captured in a viral photo, shows him playing Ludo with friends during the ceremony. This humorous scene, which sparked widespread amusement online, underscores how some moments at weddings are taken lightly, as seen also in a similar incident with a groom checking trading charts.
title: Groom playing ludo at wedding mandap leaves internet in splits

description: India displayed an impressive performance by securing a six-wicket victory against Australia PM's XI in a pink-ball warm-up match in Canberra. Shubman Gill reassured his fitness with a stylish fifty, while the team utilized all 46 overs to prepare for the upcoming pink-ball Test in Adelaide.
title: Why India batted full 46 overs despite chasing down target early

description: Shubman Gill's confident half-century highlighted India's performance in a pink-ball warm-up game against the Prime Minister's XI in Canberra, easing worries about his thumb injury. With decent contributions from Yashasvi Jaiswal and Nitish Kumar Reddy, India chased down the target of 240. Harshit Rana impressed with four key wickets, solidifying his place for the upcoming Adelaide Test.
title: Fit-again Gill shines; Rohit disappoints in warm-up

description: During a warm-up match against the Australian Prime Minister's XI, Indian pacer Mohammed Siraj humorously mimicked captain Rohit Sharma's famous one-liner, 'garden mein ghoom raha hai kya.' Siraj, who had been disrupted by a sight-screen mishap, expressed his frustration towards a security person obstructing his view, highlighting the incident while maintaining his strong performance on the field.
title: 'Garden mein ghoom raha hai kya': Siraj vents frustration

description: AAP MLA Naresh Balyan was arrested and sent to a two-day police custody in an extortion case involving gangster Kapil Sangwan. Balyan was uncooperative during questioning, prompting the arrest. AAP leader Arvind Kejriwal claimed Balyan was a victim of extortion attempts and criticized the arrest as a message against standing up to gangsters.
title: AAP MLA Naresh Balyan sent to 2-day police custody in extortion case

description: Nandan Nilekani’s decision to choose IIT Bombay over IIT Madras was an act of rebellion against his father's wishes for job security. Opting for electrical engineering shaped his future in the tech industry.
title: IIT Bombay over IIT Madras: Infosys co-founder’s 'small act of rebellion'

description: Maharashtra caretaker CM Eknath Shinde assured he is recovering well in Satara after falling ill due to an exhaustive election schedule. He confirmed his support for the party's decision on the next chief minister. Doctors have diagnosed him with a respiratory infection and recommended rest. Speculation continues about Shinde’s upcoming political decision.
title: 'Maharashtra CM decision on Monday': Shinde shares big updates

description: Vice president Jagdeep Dhankhar criticised the selective glorification in India's history, highlighting the neglect of unsung heroes like Raja Mahendra Pratap Singh in historical narratives. He called for rectifying misrepresentations and recognizing all contributions to India's independence. He also emphasised farmers' welfare as crucial for achieving the goal of a developed nation by 2047.
title: 'History manipulated': VP on 'downsizing' of some heroes of freedom struggle

description: Cyclone Fengal caused severe disruptions at Chennai International Airport, shutting it down for over 16 hours. High crosswinds and heavy rain led to the cancellation and diversion of numerous flights, stranding thousands of passengers. The airport resumed operations after 4am on December 1, as weather conditions improved.
title: Watch: Plane aborts landing just inches off runway at Chennai airport

description: Najma Heptulla, in her autobiography, recounts her ordeal of waiting an hour on an international call to inform Sonia Gandhi about her election as IPU president, only to be told 'Madam is busy.' Disappointed, Heptulla says this incident marked a turning point in her relationship with Congress, eventually leading to her joining BJP in 2004.
title: 'Madam is busy': When Najma Heptulla waited an hour on call to talk to Sonia

description: Elon Musk has filed a preliminary injunction in the US District Court for the Northern District of California to prevent OpenAI from converting to a fully for-profit entity.
title: Elon Musk goes to court to stop ChatGPT maker OpenAI's ‘biggest-ever’ move

description: A Bangladesh court will hear Hindu priest Chinmoy Krishna Das's bail plea on December 3. Das was arrested on November 27 for sedition related to hoisting a saffron flag above the national flag. His arrest incited protests and led to the freezing of accounts linked to 17 ISKCON members, amid concerns over violence targeting Hindu minorities.
title: Hindu priest held in B'desh, bail plea to be heard on Dec 3

description: Black Friday originated in Philadelphia in the 1950s and evolved into a major shopping event by the 1980s. Retailers make significant profits during this period, which extends through Cyber Monday.
title: Black Friday vs Cyber Monday in India: Dates and which day offers better discounts

description: PDP chief Mehbooba Mufti expressed concern over violence in Uttar Pradesh's Sambhal. She criticised the mosque survey and compared it to atrocities against Hindu minorities in Bangladesh. Mufti highlighted issues like poor job opportunities and infrastructure, condemning claims on Ajmer Sharif Dargah and recent mob violence against Hindu temples in Bangladesh.
title: 'No difference between India & Bangladesh': Mehbooba Mufti on Sambhal row

description: Yashasvi Jaiswal showcased his skills in the India vs Australia PM XI day-night Test at Canberra, partnering with KL Rahul to chase 241. Despite a heated moment with bowler Jack Nisbet, Jaiswal's aggressive batting stood out. Harshit Rana's 4-44 helped India restrict the Australian side to 240 in their shortened 46-overs match.
title: Watch: Yashasvi Jaiswal turns up the heat against fiery bowling

description: Tripura's Chief Minister Manik Saha raises concerns over the release of terrorists in Bangladesh and the nation's mistreatment of minorities. Recent mob attacks on Hindu temples and arrests of ISKCON priests have intensified these concerns. India has urged Bangladesh to protect minorities and ensure their safety.
title: 'Terrorists out of jail concerning as Tripura shares borders with Bangladesh': CM Saha

description: Cyclone Fengal caused severe disruptions at Chennai International Airport, shutting it down for over 16 hours. High crosswinds and heavy rain led to the cancellation and diversion of numerous flights, stranding thousands of passengers. The airport resumed operations after 4am on December 1, as weather conditions improved.
title: Watch: Plane aborts landing just inches off runway at Chennai airport

description: Virat Kohli prepares intensively for the pink ball Test against Australia, showcasing solid defense against Jasprit Bumrah in Canberra. Meanwhile, Harshit Rana's impressive 4-44 helped India bowl out the Prime Minister's XI for 240 in the reduced overs warm-up match at Manuka Oval.
title: Kohli takes on Bumrah in high-intensity nets. Watch

description: RSS chief Mohan Bhagwat expressed concerns over India's declining population, urging the need to maintain fertility rates above 2.1 for societal survival. He emphasized that lower rates could lead to the disappearance of societies and languages, referencing India's population policy from 1998 or 2002.
title: Fertility rate should not go below 2.1 for society to survive: RSS chief Mohan Bhagwat

description: The government issued an order revoking the previous constitution of the state Waqf Board due to prolonged non-functioning following a court stay. The action was prompted by litigation over the election of a board member and aimed at preventing an administrative vacuum.
title: Andhra Pradesh govt issues order to dissolve Waqf Board

description: A newlywed woman named Damini died in her in-laws' home in Bareilly after a geyser exploded while she was taking a bath. The incident occurred five days after her wedding. Despite attempts to get her to respond, family members eventually broke down the bathroom door, discovered her unconscious, and took her to the hospital where she was declared dead.
title: Days after wedding, newlywed woman dies in geyser explosion in Bareilly

description: President-elect Donald Trump has named Kash Patel as the next Director of the FBI, citing his experience as a lawyer and investigator committed to justice and transparency. Despite some Republican opposition and criticisms of being overly loyal to Trump, Patel is recognized for his efforts in exposing corruption and the alleged 'Russia Hoax.'
title: Hard Kash: Trump names loyalist Patel to head FBI

description: Rekha will grace the upcoming episode of The Great Indian Kapil Show, enchanting everyone with her elegance. Highlights include Rekha's humorous interaction with Kapil Sharma, hilarious gags by Sunil Grover and Krushna Abhishek, and a dance performance rekindling memories of Amitabh Bachchan. The previous episode saw an emotional reunion of Krushna and Govinda, marking Govinda's return after an injury.
title: Kapil Show: Rekha recreates her iconic dance number

description: India captain Rohit Sharma experimented with wicketkeeper Sarfaraz Khan in place of Rishabh Pant during a warm-up match against Australia's PM's XI. Pacer Harshit Rana impressed with figures of 4-44, restricting the PM's XI to 240. Sam Konstas stood out with a century, but Rana’s four-wicket haul helped India remain competitive.
title: Rohit Sharma tests new wicketkeeper in warm-up match

description: Suman Kumar, an 18-year-old left-arm spinner from Bihar, made history by taking all 10 wickets in an innings during the Under-19 Cooch Behar Trophy match against Rajasthan. Inspired by India's Ravindra Jadeja, Suman's remarkable performance on a batting-friendly pitch is a testament to his skill and determination, aiming to one day play for India.
title: Exclusive| Meet Suman Kumar: 'Bihar ka Jaddu'

description: During her visit to Wayanad, Congress MP Priyanka Gandhi Vadra criticised the BJP-led Central government for undermining people's rights and benefiting corporate allies. She pledged support to her constituency's residents and highlighted concerns about the erosion of national institutions. Her two-day visit included public addresses at various locations alongside Rahul Gandhi.
title: Fight is for spirit of country: Priyanka slams Centre over 'businessmen friends'

description: In Rajasthan's Kota district, a section of an under-construction tunnel on the Delhi-Mumbai Expressway collapsed, resulting in the death of one worker and injuries to two others. Emergency services rescued the trapped workers, with authorities from the National Highways Authority of India investigating the cause of the collapse.
title: 1 dead, 2 injured after section of under-construction tunnel part of Delhi-Mumbai Expressway collapses in Kota

description: Guntur excise officials lodged a case against Venkatrami Reddy, president of Andhra Pradesh Secretariat Employees’ Association, for holding an unauthorized liquor party at Kondapakaluru Gardens. The event, aimed at influencing forthcoming elections, was raided late Thursday night, leading to the seizure of seven liquor bottles. Reddy, currently suspended for political campaigning, violated excise regulations by not obtaining necessary permissions.
title: ​Excise raid: Andhra Pradesh secretariat staff leader in dock over booze party

description: The Indian team management is considering having Rohit Sharma bat in the middle-order for the upcoming pink-ball Test in Adelaide. Despite being an opener, he did not start at the top in the warm-up match. The Yashasvi Jaiswal-KL Rahul pair, which was successful in the Perth Test, is likely to continue opening.
title: Rohit to bat in middle-order in pink-ball Test?

description: The Election Commission has filed an FIR against Syed Shuja for his claims of tampering with Maharashtra's EVMs by hacking their frequency. The Maharashtra CEO termed his claims as false and unsubstantiated. The Supreme Court supports the reliability of EVMs, affirming that they are tamper-proof.
title: 'Hiding in another country': FIR against 'EVM hacker' after EC complaint

description: Arvind Kejriwal criticizes the BJP-led central government for neglecting law and order in Delhi, citing three attacks on him in 35 days, including a recent liquid-throwing incident. Kejriwal also accuses the Home Minister of targeting whistleblowers instead of addressing gangster threats, while BJP dismisses his claims as a sympathy ploy.
title: 'Third attack on me in 35 days,' says Kejriwal; BJP calls it drama

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi and Union Home Minister Amit Shah lauded the Border Security Force (BSF) on its Raising Day, highlighting its critical role in safeguarding the nation. The BSF, the world's largest border guarding force, marks its Raising Day annually on December 1, with approximately 2.65 lakh personnel ensuring the security of India's borders with Pakistan and Bangladesh.
title: 'Stands as critical line of defence': PM Modi hails BSF on Raising Day

description: Businessman Raj Kundra has been summoned by the ED for questioning about a high-profile pornography racket. Recent raids targeted multiple locations linked to Kundra in Mumbai and Uttar Pradesh. The investigation focuses on Kundra's alleged involvement in streaming explicit content via the Hotshots app, with suspicion of money laundering and international connections.
title: ED summons Raj Kundra for questioning in money laundering case

description: US Republican Vivek Ramaswamy criticized a report that New York City is paying $220 million to rent a Pakistani government-owned hotel in Manhattan to house undocumented immigrants. The Roosevelt Hotel's lease, part of a $1.1 billion IMF bailout for Pakistan, is expected to generate significant revenue for Pakistan over three years.
title: 'Nuts': Vivek Ramaswamy slams NYC's $220 million deal with Pakistani-owned hotel

description: Assam's CM Himanta Biswa Sarma is open to banning beef if Congress president Bhupen Borah formally requests it. This follows allegations that the BJP used beef distributions to win the Samaguri constituency. Sarma challenges Congress to clarify their stance, suggesting a beef ban could resolve the controversy.
title: Ready to ban beef in Assam if Congress writes to me: Himanta Biswa Sarma

description: In Bhakkar, Pakistan, a groom received a 35-foot garland made from 2,000 currency notes worth PKR 1 lakh, attracting attention on social media. The garland, featuring fresh flowers and decorative ribbons, was draped around the groom's neck, sparking varied reactions online. A similar incident occurred earlier with a 30-foot currency garland.
title: 'Wearing the GDP': Groom in Pakistan flaunts 35-foot currency garland

description: NASA has chosen SpaceX's Falcon Heavy rocket for the Dragonfly mission to Saturn's moon, Titan. Scheduled for 2028, this $3.35 billion project will send a nuclear-powered octocopter to explore Titan's habitability. Dragonfly will autonomously examine the moon's icy and dune-filled terrains for three years, analyzing its atmosphere and potential for exotic life.
title: Nasa to launch 'Dragonfly' to Saturn's moon Titan on SpaceX Falcon Heavy rocket

description: Jay Shah has commenced his tenure as the Chair of the International Cricket Council (ICC). Shah aims to enhance cricket’s global reach, especially targeting the 2028 Los Angeles Olympics, and grow the women's game. Expressing gratitude for the support, he plans to build on the achievements of his predecessor Greg Barclay.
title: Jay Shah takes charge as ICC Chair, aims to expand cricket's global reach

description: The Archaeological Survey of India (ASI) asserts its management authority over the Shahi Jama Masjid, emphasizing concerns about unauthorized alterations by the mosque's committee. A violent survey at the mosque, in light of claims of a former temple, prompted judicial investigation into the incident's nature and subsequent preventive measures.
title: Sambhal mosque: ASI seeks control of mughal era structure Shahi Jama Masjid

description: Arvind Kejriwal claimed that MLA Naresh Balyan, arrested for extortion, was victimized for filing complaints against gangster Kapil Sangwan. Balyan had reported extortion demands from Sangwan, and Kejriwal criticized the arrest as intimidation against those speaking out against criminals. Delhi police allege Balyan's involvement with Sangwan, based on an audio clip.
title: Arvind Kejriwal defends MLA Naresh Balyan, calls him 'victim' of gangster extortion

description: England clinched a significant eight-wicket victory over New Zealand in the first Test of the series in Christchurch. This win, marking their 10th in the current ICC World Test Championship cycle, boosted their PCT slightly but they still rank sixth. New Zealand's defeat affected their WTC standing, dropping to a tie for fourth place with Sri Lanka.
title: WTC standings: India maintain top spot, NZ's final hopes dented

description: Commercial LPG and aviation fuel prices in New Delhi surge following the monthly revision to align with international oil price trends. Commercial LPG rates now stand at Rs 1818.50 per 19 kg cylinder, while ATF prices in Delhi increased by Rs 1,318.12 per kl, reaching Rs 91,856.84 per kl.
title: Commercial LPG hike by Rs 16.5 per cylinder, jet fuel up 1.45%

description: Researchers in Northern Laos are combating the decline of Asian elephants, with a population plummeting from 1500 to only 500-1000 elephants due to habitat loss, logging, and limited breeding. Utilizing DNA analysis of dung, they aim to maintain genetic diversity, prevent inbreeding, and support conservation efforts.
title: Researchers to study DNA from dung to save Laos elephants

description: India's ODI and Test captain Rohit Sharma and his wife Ritika Sajdeh have named their newborn son Ahaan. The couple welcomed their second child in November this year. Ritika shared the name via an Instagram Story. Rohit is currently in Canberra with the team, set to play the second Test in Adelaide on December 6.
title: Revealed! Name of Rohit Sharma, Ritika Sajdeh's son

description: Belka, a loyal Russian dog, remained at the site where her owner drowned in the Ufa River. The man fell through thin ice and was swept away by a strong current. Despite family efforts to bring her home, Belka tirelessly returned to the riverbank, reminiscent of Japan’s Hachiko. The tragic incident highlights the dangers of crossing thin ice.
title: 'Russian Hachikō': Dog waits four days on ice for owner who drowned at the spot

description: Kash Patel’s views on global and domestic issues stand out for their marked divergence from those of the US establishment and mainstream media. Patel, an Indian-American and Trump loyalist, has been vocal in his support for the Ram Temple in Ayodhya, citing historical significance that he argues has been ignored by Western narratives. His remarks challenge what he describes as a "disinformation campaign" targeting India and Prime Minister Narendra Modi.
title: 'Hindu temple there for 500 years': When Trump's FBI chief pick supported Ram Mandir

description: Russia successfully launched the Soyuz-2.1a rocket, placing the Kondor-FKA2 radar satellite into orbit from the Vostochny Cosmodrome. The satellite, with advanced radar technology, is capable of all-weather, round-the-clock Earth observation, and its mission includes mapping, environmental monitoring, and guiding vessels through ice-covered routes. The Kondor series continues to advance with more launches scheduled.
title: Russia launches Kondor-FKA2 radar satellite into orbit

description: Seven CPI Maoists, including two key state committee members, were killed in an encounter with Telangana Greyhounds in Eturunagaram, Mulugu district. The clash followed the Maoists' earlier killing of two tribals, accused of being police informers. Recovered from the scene were two AK-47 rifles. These events were reviewed by Mulugu superintendent of police Shabarish.
title: 7 Maoists killed in encounter in Telangana's Mulugu, 2 AK-47 rifles recovered

description: Cyclonic storm Fengal crossed the North Tamil Nadu and Puducherry coasts early Sunday, bringing heavy rainfall, high winds, and rough seas. The Veedur Dam in Tamil Nadu overflowed, flooding risk to nearby villages. In Chennai, airport operations halted and several flights were canceled. IMD expects Fengal to weaken into a deep depression as it moves westwards.
title: Watch: Veedur dam overflows as Cyclone Fengal hits TN, 10 villages at flood risk

description: England won the first Test against New Zealand by eight wickets in Christchurch. They chased down 104 runs in just 12.4 overs, setting records for speed and run rate. Brydon Carse took six wickets, and Jacob Bethell scored a quick fifty. England lead the series 1-0 with the second Test starting in Wellington on Friday.
title: England smash record for fastest run chase in Test history

description: Dua Lipa performed in Mumbai and surprised fans with a mash-up of her song 'Levitating' and Shah Rukh Khan’s 'Woh Ladki Jo'. The performance quickly went viral. Shah Rukh Khan’s daughter Suhana Khan shared her excitement on Instagram. This was Dua Lipa’s third visit to India, and she shared her appreciation for Indian culture.
title: Suhana Khan can't get enough of Dua Lipa's 'Levitating' mash-up 'Woh Ladki Jo'

description: OpenAI is sued by five Canadian news companies, including the Globe and Mail and CBC/Radio-Canada, for copyright infringement. The lawsuit claims that OpenAI used their news articles to train ChatGPT without authorisation.
title: ChatGPT maker OpenAI faces copyright infringement lawsuit in Canada

description: A bustling week in the tech sphere featured the launch of Realme GT 7 Pro with Snapdragon 8 Elite chipset in India, a contempt notice issued to Google CEO Sundar Pichai, and Infosys announcing an 85% performance bonus. The CCI initiated a probe against Google, and the government introduced PAN 2.0 to tackle fraudulent activities.
title: Google CEO’s Mumbai court notice, Infosys bonus, other tech news

description: At the launch of Vikram Sampath's book on Tipu Sultan, EAM S Jaishankar emphasizes the complex legacy of Tipu Sultan, noting both his resistance to British colonization and the controversies of his rule. He advocates for objective historical accounts, highlighting the influence of contemporary politics on historical narratives.
title: Tipu Sultan anti-British but evokes strong adverse sentiments: Jaishankar

description: The men's Survivor Series WarGames match featured intense action and dramatic moments. Jacob Fatu's agility shined, while Solo Sikoa's tactics caused chaos. Roman Reigns' climactic spear on Solo secured victory for his team, despite accidental and high-risk stunts involving CM Punk, Reed, and Jimmy Uso.
title: WWE Survivor Series WarGames: Roman Reigns and others beat the new Bloodline

description: Mohammed Shami is being assessed for his match fitness in case he is required to join India's Test squad in Australia. BCCI officials and NCA's Sports Science team are monitoring his performance during the Syed Mushtaq Ali Trophy in Rajkot to ensure he meets the physical demands required for high-intensity matches.
title: Shami's fitness being closely monitored by selector in Rajkot

description: A woman employed at a pharma company was coerced by cyber fraudsters posing as Delhi Police officers. They claimed she was involved in a money laundering probe, and forced her to strip during a video call for supposed 'body verification'. The incident occurred in late November, leading to an FIR registration. The fraudsters also managed to swindle Rs 1.
title: Mumbai woman made to strip, loses Rs 1.7 lakh after 'digital arrest' threat

description: PCB agrees to a hybrid model for ICC Champions Trophy, with India playing matches in Dubai due to security reasons. PCB demands equal terms for future tournaments in India, seeks larger ICC revenue share. BCCI remains firm on hybrid model. Final decisions expected soon, with Jay Shah's upcoming ICC chairmanship influencing the resolution.
title: Pakistan agrees to hybrid model for Champions Trophy

description: A Delhi Police head constable was stabbed by a known criminal, Mohammed Adil, in New Usmanpur during a patrol. Adil, who has a history of criminal activities, was shot and apprehended by the police. This incident follows the fatal stabbing of another constable in Govindpuri, highlighting recent attacks on law enforcement officers in Delhi.
title: Week after murder, another Delhi cop stabbed by criminal

description: A 24-year-old woman, Meera, was shot dead by her boyfriend, Sachin Yadav, in a failed suicide pact in Chhatarpur, MP. Despite planning to kill himself, Sachin lost his nerve and fled the scene before being arrested. The couple faced strong family opposition to their relationship.
title: Twist in lover's suicide pact in MP: Youth shoots girl, then changes his mind

description: Joe Root has broken the record for the most fourth-innings runs in Test cricket, surpassing Sachin Tendulkar. Root achieved this milestone during England's successful chase against New Zealand. Root now holds 1630 runs, ahead of Tendulkar's 1625. This feat was accomplished in his 150th Test, adding to his already impressive career accomplishments.
title: Joe Root surpasses Sachin Tendulkar for this big record in Test cricket

description: Despite a 70% reduction in stubble burning incidents in Punjab and a 42% reduction in Haryana, farm fires remain a significant contributor to Delhi's pollution levels. This is due to the persistent north-westerly winds and poor air ventilation in the city, highlighting the complexity of addressing air quality issues.
title: Farm fires at record low but impact on Delhi air still high

description: Vice President-elect JD Vance, an Ohio State University alum, is criticized for his supportive social media post to Ohio State senior players after their loss to Michigan. Wolverines supporters responded mockingly, targeting Vance's political identity and the team's performance.
title: JD Vance trolled for supporting Ohio State after losing game to Michigan in 'The Game'

description: Violent clashes erupted in Tbilisi as protesters opposed the Georgian government's decision to delay EU membership talks amid a post-election crisis. Demonstrations against the ruling Georgian Dream party's declared victory led to arrests and confrontations with police using rubber bullets and tear gas. President Salome Zurabishvili called for stability, while international condemnation of the crackdown mounted.
title: Clashes erupt outside Georgia parliament between pro-EU protesters & police

description: Cristiano Ronaldo collaborated with YouTube sensation MrBeast in a video where they competed in a football challenge. The challenge involved hitting cardboard cutouts of MrBeast from various distances. Adding to the excitement, they wagered their YouTube subscribers on the outcome of the challenge, drawing significant viewer engagement within hours of release.
title: Ronaldo vs MrBeast: The most insane challenge on YouTube!

description: A 65-year-old man, Ram Jiyawan, died after falling from a moving AC bus while trying to spit tobacco near Beehi village on Purvanchal Expressway. The bus was en route from Lucknow to Azamgarh. Despite medical attention, he succumbed to injuries. His family requested no further investigation, but police will conduct a preliminary inquiry.
title: Man falls to death while spitting tobacco from moving bus in Uttar Pradesh

description: US President-elect Donald Trump appointed Kashyap 'Kash' Patel as the head of the FBI, emphasizing Patel's experience and pledge to restore fidelity, bravery, and integrity. Patel held notable positions during Trump's first term and played key roles in exposing perceived corruption and defending the American people.
title: Donald Trump picks Indian-American Kash Patel to lead FBI

description: A Bulandshahr court has sentenced Radha Devi to life imprisonment for murdering her husband Jogendra Kumar in 2022. Her 6-year-old son's testimony was crucial. Radha's lover Kanhaiya Kumar, her father Yogendra Singh, and her brother Anuj Kumar also received life sentences for their roles in the crime.
title: 6-year-old son's testimony gets woman life term for killing hubby in UP
After public outcry, Railways says blankets washed twice a month
HIV positive patients under treatment up by 3 lakh in 4 years

description: A man named Ashok Jha threw liquid on Arvind Kejriwal during a padayatra in Malviya Nagar. The accused, claimed to be a BJP worker, allegedly intended to set Kejriwal on fire. He was caught and detained by police. AAP accused BJP of being behind the attack and expressed concern over rising crime.
title: 'Attempt to burn him alive': AAP minister after man hurls liquid at Arvind Kejriwal

description: Social activist Baba Adhav ended his hunger strike after Uddhav Thackeray assured a push for fair election procedures. Adhav had questioned the assembly poll results, alleging misuse of money power, while Ajit Pawar defended the use of EVMs, citing previous Lok Sabha results accepted without dispute.
title: Baba Adhav ends hunger strike after Uddhav Thackeray's assurance
